Nigeria now has 53,865 confirmed COVID-19 cases, with 138 new cases recorded on Sunday night According to a tweet from the Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, 41,513 patients have now been discharged, with 1,013 patients losing their lives to the Coronavirus pandemic. The tweet revealed that Plateau state again has the highest number of infections on Sunday night with 55 cases, with Lagos state following with 15 cases. Other states read as follows: Ebonyi-11 Oyo-11 Abia-8 Anambra-7 FCT-7 Rivers-7 Kaduna-6 Ondo-5 Kwara-3 Bauchi-1 Benue-1 Edo-1 138 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Plateau-55Lagos-15Ebonyi-11Oyo-11Abia-8Anambra-7FCT-7Rivers-7Kaduna-6Ondo-5Kwara-3Bauchi-1Benue-1Edo-1 53,865 confirmed41,513 discharged1,013 deaths pic.twitter.com/HfTvUqmYXc — NCDC (@NCDCgov) August 30, 2020 